Both required files are emitted in the working directory:

- **transcript.json** — 25 iterations, schema-validated, walking from prognostic biomarker scans (iters 1-5) → main treatment effects + randomization check (6-7) → ven_aza × biomarker interactions (8-12, 16) → other-treatment subgroup screens (13-15, 22) → adjusted multivariable model (17) → tightening multi-feature ven_aza subgroups (18-21) → tree/rule confirmation (23) → final positive and null subgroup statements (24-25).
- **analysis_summary.txt** — narrative synthesis of which hypotheses were supported (NPM1 +6.7pp, unfit +5.6pp, ven_aza +5.4pp; ven_aza × NPM1 / × unfit positive interactions; ven_aza × TP53 / × CK negative interactions) and refuted (FLT3-targeted drugs, IDH-targeted drugs, and 7+3 show no positive biomarker-defined subgroup).

**Headline finding:** treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine is the only treatment with a real effect on objective_response. The maximal-benefit subgroup is **npm1_mutation==1 AND unfit_for_intensive==1 AND tp53_mutation==0 AND complex_karyotype==0** (78.6% on vs 15.8% off, +62.8pp, p<1e-300). The suppression rule **tp53_mutation==1 OR complex_karyotype==1** abolishes the effect (+0.6pp, p=0.36).
